The article is a statement by the President of the United States, congratulating Yoshihiko Noda on his election as Japan's next prime minister. The President expresses his commitment to working with Noda and the Japanese people on initiatives that benefit both countries, the region, and the world. He highlights the importance of the U.S.-Japan Alliance in maintaining peace and security in the Asia Pacific region and expresses his desire to continue this stability and prosperity in the coming years. The President also emphasizes the relationship between the United States and Japan, based on common interests and values, and expresses his willingness to collaborate with Prime Minister Noda on various economic and security issues.